  "prompt": "How do you get an ink stain out of fabric?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to remove ink stains from fabric:\n\n1. Rubbing Alcohol Method\n- Dab rubbing alcohol onto the stain with a clean cloth\n- Blot, don't rub\n- Wash the fabric as normal\n\n2. Hairspray Method\n- Spray hairspray directly on the stain\n- Let sit for a few minutes\n- Blot with a clean cloth\n- Wash normally\n\n3. Hand Sanitizer Method\n- Apply hand sanitizer to the stain\n- Let sit for a few minutes\n- Blot with a clean cloth\n- Wash normally\n\n4. Milk Method\n- Soak the stained area in milk overnight\n- Wash the next day\n\n5. White Vinegar Method\n- Mix equal parts white vinegar and water\n- Dab onto the stain\n- Blot with a clean cloth\n- Wash normally\n\nTips:\n- Act quickly for best results\n- Test any method on a small, hidden area first\n- Don't put the fabric in the dryer until the stain is completely gone\n- For delicate fabrics, consider professional cleaning\n\nDifferent methods work better on different types of ink and fabrics.",
